Research consistently shows:

# Comprehension

is:

```text id="p5m9qe"
making meaning
```

—not merely reading words.

Students learn:

```text id="x2v4qe"
listen/read
→ understand
→ sequence
→ retell
→ explain
```

Story retelling develops:

* memory
* sequencing
* oral language
* comprehension
* narrative reasoning

This becomes:

# Story Thinking

Children who retell stories tend to show stronger comprehension and language development.

